.SH "CALLBACK ABI"
.IX Header "CALLBACK ABI"
Watcher callbacks receive:
.PP
.Vb 1
\&  $cb\->($loop, $fh, $watcher)
.Ve
.SS "Error readiness ordering"
.IX Subsection "Error readiness ordering"
If an epoll event indicates an error condition (for example \f(CW\*(C`EPOLLERR\*(C'\fR), the loop
dispatches to the watcher\*(Aqs \f(CW\*(C`error\*(C'\fR callback first (if installed and enabled)
and returns.
.PP
If no \f(CW\*(C`error\*(C'\fR callback is installed/enabled, error readiness may be treated as
readable and/or writable (depending on the platform and backend behavior). Do not
rely on a specific fallback; install an \f(CW\*(C`error\*(C'\fR handler if you want explicit
error handling.
.SS "Hangup / EOF"
.IX Subsection "Hangup / EOF"
On hangup conditions (for example \f(CW\*(C`EPOLLHUP\*(C'\fR), readable readiness is typically
delivered so user code can observe EOF via \f(CWread(2)\fR returning 0.
